---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="MongoDB WiredTiger Storage Engine: Internals Visualized" 
  description="Interactive visualization of WiredTiger — B-Tree pages, MVCC snapshots, checkpointing, cache eviction, compression, and journal (WAL)"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/" }, 
    { label: "MongoDB", href: "/mongodb/" },
    { label: "WiredTiger Storage", href: "/mongodb/wiredtiger/" }
  ]}
>
  <div class="viz-container">
    <header class="viz-header">
      <h1>🍃 WiredTiger Storage Engine</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How MongoDB Stores, Caches, and Recovers Your Data</p>
    </header>

    <section class="overview-section">
      <div class="overview-card">
        <p>
          WiredTiger is MongoDB's default storage engine since 3.2. It uses a <strong>B-Tree</strong> index structure
          (not LSM-Tree like RocksDB), provides <em>document-level concurrency</em> via MVCC snapshots,
          and ensures durability through <strong>write-ahead journaling</strong> with periodic checkpoints.
          Understanding its internals — page structure, cache management, and compression — is key to tuning MongoDB performance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- B-Tree vs LSM-Tree -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>🌳 B-Tree vs LSM-Tree</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">WiredTiger chose B-Tree for MongoDB's random-read-heavy workloads. Compare both structures side by side.</p>

      <div class="sim-controls">
        <div class="sim-actions">
          <button id="treeWriteBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">✏️ Write Key</button>
          <button id="treeReadBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">🔍 Read Key</button>
          <button id="treeBurstBtn" class="action-btn balance-btn">⚡ Burst 10 Writes</button>
          <button id="treeResetBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tree-compare">
        <div class="tree-panel">
          <div class="tree-panel-header btree-header">B-Tree (WiredTiger)</div>
          <div class="tree-canvas" id="btreeCanvas"></div>
          <div class="tree-stats">
            <div class="stat-card"><span class="stat-label">Writes</span><span class="stat-value" id="btreeWrites">0</span></div>
            <div class="stat-card"><span class="stat-label">Reads</span><span class="stat-value" id="btreeReads">0</span></div>
            <div class="stat-card"><span class="stat-label">Read Cost</span><span class="stat-value" id="btreeReadCost">O(log n)</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="tree-note good-note">✅ In-place updates, fast point reads by _id</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tree-panel">
          <div class="tree-panel-header lsm-header">LSM-Tree (RocksDB-style)</div>
          <div class="tree-canvas" id="lsmCanvas"></div>
          <div class="tree-stats">
            <div class="stat-card"><span class="stat-label">Writes</span><span class="stat-value" id="lsmWrites">0</span></div>
            <div class="stat-card"><span class="stat-label">Reads</span><span class="stat-value" id="lsmReads">0</span></div>
            <div class="stat-card"><span class="stat-label">Read Cost</span><span class="stat-value" id="lsmReadCost">O(k·log n)</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="tree-note warn-note">⚠️ Append-only writes (fast), but reads check multiple levels</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="sim-log" id="treeLog">
        <div class="log-entry">Ready. Write and read keys to compare B-Tree vs LSM behavior.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Page Structure -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>📄 Page Structure</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">WiredTiger organizes data in a B-Tree of pages — internal (branch) pages route to leaf pages that hold documents.</p>

      <div class="page-tree-container">
        <div class="page-tree" id="pageTree">
          <div class="page-level">
            <div class="page-node root-page" data-page="root" id="pageRoot">
              <div class="page-type">Root (Internal)</div>
              <div class="page-size">4KB</div>
              <div class="page-keys">keys: [F, N]</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="page-connectors">
            <svg width="100%" height="30" class="connector-svg">
              <line x1="25%" y1="0" x2="16.6%" y2="30" stroke="#555" stroke-width="1.5"></line>
              <line x1="50%" y1="0" x2="50%" y2="30" stroke="#555" stroke-width="1.5"></line>
              <line x1="75%" y1="0" x2="83.3%" y2="30" stroke="#555" stroke-width="1.5"></line>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="page-level">
            <div class="page-node internal-page" data-page="int-left" id="pageIntLeft">
              <div class="page-type">Internal</div>
              <div class="page-size">4KB</div>
              <div class="page-keys">keys: [C]</div>
            </div>
            <div class="page-node internal-page" data-page="int-mid" id="pageIntMid">
              <div class="page-type">Internal</div>
              <div class="page-size">4KB</div>
              <div class="page-keys">keys: [J]</div>
            </div>
            <div class="page-node internal-page" data-page="int-right" id="pageIntRight">
              <div class="page-type">Internal</div>
              <div class="page-size">4KB</div>
              <div class="page-keys">keys: [R]</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="page-connectors">
            <svg width="100%" height="30" class="connector-svg">
              <line x1="8.3%" y1="0" x2="8.3%" y2="30" stroke="#555" stroke-width="1"></line>
              <line x1="16.6%" y1="0" x2="25%" y2="30" stroke="#555" stroke-width="1"></line>
              <line x1="41.6%" y1="0" x2="41.6%" y2="30" stroke="#555" stroke-width="1"></line>
              <line x1="50%" y1="0" x2="58.3%" y2="30" stroke="#555" stroke-width="1"></line>
              <line x1="75%" y1="0" x2="75%" y2="30" stroke="#555" stroke-width="1"></line>
              <line x1="83.3%" y1="0" x2="91.6%" y2="30" stroke="#555" stroke-width="1"></line>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="page-level leaf-level">
            <div class="page-node leaf-page" data-page="leaf-0" id="pageLeaf0">
              <div class="page-type">Leaf</div>
              <div class="page-size">32KB</div>
              <div class="page-docs">A, B</div>
            </div>
            <div class="page-node leaf-page" data-page="leaf-1" id="pageLeaf1">
              <div class="page-type">Leaf</div>
              <div class="page-size">32KB</div>
              <div class="page-docs">C, D, E</div>
            </div>
            <div class="page-node leaf-page" data-page="leaf-2" id="pageLeaf2">
              <div class="page-type">Leaf</div>
              <div class="page-size">32KB</div>
              <div class="page-docs">F, G, H</div>
            </div>
            <div class="page-node leaf-page" data-page="leaf-3" id="pageLeaf3">
              <div class="page-type">Leaf</div>
              <div class="page-size">32KB</div>
              <div class="page-docs">J, K, L, M</div>
            </div>
            <div class="page-node leaf-page" data-page="leaf-4" id="pageLeaf4">
              <div class="page-type">Leaf</div>
              <div class="page-size">32KB</div>
              <div class="page-docs">N, O, P, Q</div>
            </div>
            <div class="page-node leaf-page" data-page="leaf-5" id="pageLeaf5">
              <div class="page-type">Leaf</div>
              <div class="page-size">32KB</div>
              <div class="page-docs">R, S, T, U</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="page-inspector" id="pageInspector">
          <div class="inspector-title">🔍 Click a page to inspect</div>
          <div class="inspector-body" id="inspectorBody">
            <p class="inspector-hint">Select any page in the tree above to see its internal structure and metadata.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MVCC & Snapshots -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>📸 MVCC &amp; Snapshots</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">WiredTiger stores multiple document versions with transaction timestamps. Reads use point-in-time snapshots.</p>

      <div class="sim-controls">
        <div class="sim-actions">
          <button id="mvccWriteBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">✏️ Write (Txn)</button>
          <button id="mvccReadBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">🔍 Snapshot Read</button>
          <button id="mvccConcurrentBtn" class="action-btn balance-btn">🔀 Concurrent Ops</button>
          <button id="mvccResetBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mvcc-container">
        <div class="mvcc-doc">
          <div class="mvcc-doc-header">Document: user_42</div>
          <div class="mvcc-versions" id="mvccVersions">
            <div class="mvcc-version current-version">
              <div class="version-ts">ts: 1</div>
              <div class="version-data">&#123; name: "Alice", age: 30 &#125;</div>
              <div class="version-badge">current</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mvcc-snapshots" id="mvccSnapshots">
          <div class="snapshot-header">Active Snapshots</div>
          <div class="snapshot-list" id="snapshotList">
            <div class="snapshot-empty">No active snapshots. Click "Snapshot Read" to create one.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="sim-log" id="mvccLog">
        <div class="log-entry">Ready. Write to create new versions, read to take snapshots.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Checkpointing -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>💾 Checkpointing</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Every 60 seconds (or 2GB of journal data), WiredTiger flushes all dirty pages to disk and creates a new consistent root.</p>

      <div class="checkpoint-controls">
        <button id="cpWriteBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">✏️ Dirty Write</button>
        <button id="cpCheckpointBtn" class="action-btn balance-btn">💾 Checkpoint!</button>
        <button id="cpCrashBtn" class="action-btn crash-btn">💥 Simulate Crash</button>
        <button id="cpResetBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
      </div>

      <div class="checkpoint-viz">
        <div class="cp-section-col">
          <div class="cp-label">WiredTiger Cache (Memory)</div>
          <div class="cp-pages" id="cpPages">
            <div class="cp-page clean">Page A <span class="cp-status">clean</span></div>
            <div class="cp-page clean">Page B <span class="cp-status">clean</span></div>
            <div class="cp-page clean">Page C <span class="cp-status">clean</span></div>
            <div class="cp-page clean">Page D <span class="cp-status">clean</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cp-arrow" id="cpArrow">⬇️</div>
        <div class="cp-section-col">
          <div class="cp-label">On Disk</div>
          <div class="cp-disk" id="cpDisk">
            <div class="cp-disk-item">Checkpoint #0 (initial) — all clean</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cp-stats">
        <div class="stat-card"><span class="stat-label">Dirty Pages</span><span class="stat-value" id="cpDirtyCount">0</span></div>
        <div class="stat-card"><span class="stat-label">Checkpoints</span><span class="stat-value" id="cpCount">0</span></div>
        <div class="stat-card"><span class="stat-label">Journal Entries</span><span class="stat-value" id="cpJournalCount">0</span></div>
      </div>

      <div class="sim-log" id="cpLog">
        <div class="log-entry">Ready. Write to dirty pages, then checkpoint to flush to disk.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Cache & Eviction -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>🧊 Cache &amp; Eviction</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">WiredTiger uses its own cache (default: 50% of RAM - 1GB). When it fills up, eviction kicks in — clean pages first, then dirty.</p>

      <div class="sim-controls">
        <div class="sim-actions">
          <button id="cacheLoadBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">📥 Load Page</button>
          <button id="cacheBurstBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">⚡ Burst Load</button>
          <button id="cacheDirtyBtn" class="action-btn balance-btn">🖊️ Dirty Write</button>
          <button id="cacheResetBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cache-viz">
        <div class="cache-meter-container">
          <div class="cache-meter-label">Cache Usage</div>
          <div class="cache-meter">
            <div class="cache-meter-fill" id="cacheFill"></div>
            <div class="cache-meter-target" id="cacheTarget" title="Eviction target (80%)"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="cache-meter-info">
            <span id="cacheUsed">0</span> / <span id="cacheMax">16</span> pages
            <span class="cache-pct" id="cachePct">0%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cache-slots" id="cacheSlots"></div>
        <div class="cache-legend">
          <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot clean-dot"></span> Clean</span>
          <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot dirty-dot"></span> Dirty</span>
          <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot empty-dot"></span> Empty</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="sim-log" id="cacheLog">
        <div class="log-entry">Ready. Load pages into cache. When it fills past 80%, eviction begins.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Compression -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>🗜️ Compression</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">WiredTiger supports block compression (snappy, zlib, zstd) and prefix key compression. Trade CPU for disk space.</p>

      <div class="compression-demo">
        <div class="comp-input">
          <div class="comp-label">Original Data (1000 documents, ~48KB)</div>
          <div class="comp-bar original-bar">
            <div class="comp-fill" style="width: 100%;">48 KB</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="comp-results" id="compResults">
          <div class="comp-row">
            <div class="comp-algo">
              <span class="comp-name">None</span>
              <span class="comp-desc">No compression</span>
            </div>
            <div class="comp-bar-wrap">
              <div class="comp-bar"><div class="comp-fill comp-none" style="width: 100%;">48 KB</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="comp-metrics">
              <span class="comp-ratio">1.0x</span>
              <span class="comp-cpu">⚡ 0ms CPU</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="comp-row">
            <div class="comp-algo">
              <span class="comp-name active-algo">Snappy (default)</span>
              <span class="comp-desc">Fast, moderate ratio</span>
            </div>
            <div class="comp-bar-wrap">
              <div class="comp-bar"><div class="comp-fill comp-snappy" style="width: 58%;">28 KB</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="comp-metrics">
              <span class="comp-ratio">1.7x</span>
              <span class="comp-cpu">⚡ 0.3ms CPU</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="comp-row">
            <div class="comp-algo">
              <span class="comp-name">zlib</span>
              <span class="comp-desc">Slower, better ratio</span>
            </div>
            <div class="comp-bar-wrap">
              <div class="comp-bar"><div class="comp-fill comp-zlib" style="width: 35%;">17 KB</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="comp-metrics">
              <span class="comp-ratio">2.8x</span>
              <span class="comp-cpu">🐢 2.1ms CPU</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="comp-row">
            <div class="comp-algo">
              <span class="comp-name">zstd</span>
              <span class="comp-desc">Best balance</span>
            </div>
            <div class="comp-bar-wrap">
              <div class="comp-bar"><div class="comp-fill comp-zstd" style="width: 30%;">14 KB</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="comp-metrics">
              <span class="comp-ratio">3.4x</span>
              <span class="comp-cpu">⚡ 0.5ms CPU</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="comp-toggle-area">
          <label>Simulate with data type:</label>
          <div class="key-buttons">
            <button class="key-btn active" data-comp="json" id="compJson">📄 JSON Documents</button>
            <button class="key-btn" data-comp="binary" id="compBinary">🔢 Binary/Images</button>
            <button class="key-btn" data-comp="text" id="compText">📝 Text-heavy</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="comp-prefix">
          <h4>🔑 Prefix Key Compression</h4>
          <div class="prefix-demo">
            <div class="prefix-before">
              <div class="prefix-label">Without prefix compression:</div>
              <code>user:alice:profile</code><br>
              <code>user:alice:settings</code><br>
              <code>user:alice:sessions</code><br>
              <span class="prefix-size">54 bytes</span>
            </div>
            <div class="prefix-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="prefix-after">
              <div class="prefix-label">With prefix compression:</div>
              <code>[user:alice:]profile</code><br>
              <code>[↑ prefix]settings</code><br>
              <code>[↑ prefix]sessions</code><br>
              <span class="prefix-size">34 bytes (37% saved)</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Journal (WAL) -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>📝 Journal (Write-Ahead Log)</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Every write goes to the journal first. Synced every 50ms (or immediately with j:true). On crash, replay from last checkpoint.</p>

      <div class="sim-controls">
        <div class="sim-actions">
          <button id="walWriteBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">✏️ Write (j:false)</button>
          <button id="walWriteSyncBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">✏️ Write (j:true)</button>
          <button id="walSyncBtn" class="action-btn balance-btn">⏱️ 50ms Sync</button>
          <button id="walResetBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="wal-viz">
        <div class="wal-flow">
          <div class="wal-stage">
            <div class="wal-stage-label">1. Application Write</div>
            <div class="wal-stage-box" id="walApp">
              <div class="wal-pending" id="walPending">0 pending</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="wal-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="wal-stage">
            <div class="wal-stage-label">2. Journal Buffer</div>
            <div class="wal-stage-box" id="walBuffer">
              <div class="wal-buffer-entries" id="walBufferEntries"></div>
              <div class="wal-pending" id="walBufferCount">0 entries</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="wal-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="wal-stage">
            <div class="wal-stage-label">3. Journal on Disk</div>
            <div class="wal-stage-box synced-box" id="walDisk">
              <div class="wal-pending" id="walDiskCount">0 synced</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="wal-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="wal-stage">
            <div class="wal-stage-label">4. Checkpoint</div>
            <div class="wal-stage-box checkpoint-box" id="walCheckpoint">
              <div class="wal-pending" id="walCpCount">0 checkpoints</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="sim-log" id="walLog">
        <div class="log-entry">Ready. Writes go to journal buffer first, then sync to disk.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Ops Best Practices -->
    <section class="ops-section">
      <h2>🛠️ Operational Best Practices</h2>
      <div class="ops-grid">
        <div class="ops-card">
          <h4>📊 Cache Statistics</h4>
          <code>db.serverStatus().wiredTiger.cache</code>
          <p>Monitor "bytes currently in the cache" vs "maximum bytes configured". Alert if eviction can't keep up.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ops-card">
          <h4>🗜️ Collection Compression</h4>
          <code>db.createCollection("c", &#123;storageEngine: &#123;wiredTiger: &#123;configString: "block_compressor=zstd"&#125;&#125;&#125;)</code>
          <p>Use zstd for best size/speed tradeoff. Snappy is default for backward compatibility.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ops-card">
          <h4>💾 Force Checkpoint</h4>
          <code>db.adminCommand(&#123;fsync: 1&#125;)</code>
          <p>Forces an immediate checkpoint. Useful before backups or maintenance windows.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ops-card">
          <h4>📏 Cache Size Tuning</h4>
          <code>storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.cacheSizeGB</code>
          <p>Default: 50% of (RAM - 1GB). Increase for read-heavy workloads; decrease if sharing with other processes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ops-card">
          <h4>📈 Eviction Monitoring</h4>
          <code>db.serverStatus().wiredTiger.cache["tracked dirty bytes in the cache"]</code>
          <p>If dirty bytes stay above 5% of cache, writes are outpacing eviction. Consider more RAM or reducing write rate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ops-card">
          <h4>🔍 Table Stats</h4>
          <code>db.collection.stats().wiredTiger</code>
          <p>Shows B-Tree depth, page counts, overflow pages, and per-collection compression ratio.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="viz-footer">
      <p>Based on <a href="https://source.wiredtiger.com/develop/arch-index.html" target="_blank">WiredTiger Architecture Guide</a> and <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/core/wiredtiger/" target="_blank">MongoDB WiredTiger Docs</a></p>
    </footer>

    <div class="share-buttons">
      <span>Share this visualization:</span>
      <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Interactive%20WiredTiger%20Storage%20Engine%20Visualizer%20-%20see%20how%20MongoDB%20stores%20data%20internally&url=https://systeminternals.dev/mongodb/wiredtiger/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">𝕏 Twitter</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://systeminternals.dev/mongodb/wiredtiger/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">in LinkedIn</a>
      <a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/submitlink?u=https://systeminternals.dev/mongodb/wiredtiger/&t=Interactive%20WiredTiger%20Storage%20Engine%20Visualizer" target="_blank" class="share-btn">🟧 HN</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .viz-container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .viz-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .viz-header h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 10px; background: linear-gradient(90deg, #22c55e, #4ade80, #86efac); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; background-clip: text; }
  .subtitle { color: #888; font-size: 1.1rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .section-desc { color: #888; margin-bottom: 24px; }

  .overview-section { margin-bottom: 50px; }
  .overview-card { background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(34,197,94,0.1), rgba(74,222,128,0.05)); border: 1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.3); border-radius: 16px; padding: 24px 28px; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: #ccc; }
  .overview-card strong { color: #fff; }
  .overview-card em { color: #4ade80; font-style: normal; font-weight: 500; }

  .action-btn { padding: 10px 20px; border: none; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; }
